AIM
To study and implement Regular Expression operations such as match(), search(), findall(), finditer(), split(), sub() and to validate date format (DD/MM/YYYY) using Python.

ALGORITHM
Part A: Regular Expression
Start the program
Import re module
Initialize a string
Print original text
Use re.match() to check starting word
Use re.search() to find first number
Use re.findall() to find all numbers
Use re.finditer() to display values with positions
Use re.split() to split string
Use re.sub() to replace numbers
Display all results

Part B: Date Validation
Take input date from user
Define pattern for DD/MM/YYYY
Check using re.match()
If match → print valid
Else → print invalid
Stop
